  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This ring is made from a thin strip of polymer clay wrapped around a round form. Pressed dried flower petals sit flush into the outer surface. A thick marker pen or a short dowel makes a good forming tool. Pick one close to the ring size you want."
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "polymer-clay"
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "polymer clay"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " wrapped around a cylindrical mandrel to size, with pressed dried flower petals embedded flush into the outer surface. A thick marker pen, a short section of wooden dowel, or any round object close to the desired ring diameter serves as the forming tool."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "infoPanel",
        "attrs": {
          "type": "warning",
          "content": "Use a dedicated oven tray. Do not share with food-prep cookware. Use fully dried, pressed botanicals only — fresh material releases moisture during curing and creates bubbles."
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "suppliesCard",
        "attrs": {
          "heading": "What you need",
          "items": [
            {
              "name": "Polymer clay, any colour",
              "quantity": "20 g",
              "substitution": null
            },
            {
              "name": "Pressed, dried flower petals or small leaves",
              "quantity": "5-8 pieces",
              "substitution": null
            },
            {
              "name": "Pottery rolling pin",
              "quantity": "1",
              "substitution": null
            },
            {
              "name": "Fettling knife",
              "quantity": "1",
              "substitution": "Sharp craft knife"
            },
            {
              "name": "Thick marker pen, dowel, or similar mandrel",
              "quantity": "1",
              "substitution": null
            },
            {
              "name": "Oven with dedicated tray",
              "quantity": "1",
              "substitution": null
            },
            {
              "name": "600-grit wet-and-dry sandpaper (optional)",
              "quantity": "1 sheet",
              "substitution": null
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Rolling and embedding the petals"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Condition the clay thoroughly until smooth. Roll to a sheet 2 mm thick."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Arrange the pressed petals across the sheet, spacing them evenly."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Roll once lightly across the petal-covered area with the rolling pin to press the petals flush with the clay surface."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Cut a strip 8 mm wide. Measure the length by wrapping it around the mandrel once and adding 5 mm for overlap."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Forming the ring"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Wrap the strip petal-side outward around the mandrel. Press the overlapping ends firmly together and smooth the join with a fingertip until no seam is visible. Slide the ring slightly on the mandrel to check it moves freely; if it feels tight, gently ease it off and re-wrap slightly looser."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Curing and finishing"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Leave the ring on the mandrel and place both on a dedicated tray. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "curing"
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "Cure"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " at 130°C for 20 minutes. Cool fully on the mandrel before removing. Sand the inside of the band lightly with 600-grit sandpaper under running water if any roughness remains at the join."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Variations"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Use translucent polymer clay so the petals show as shadows viewed from any angle."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Make a matching set of rings in graduated widths from one petal-decorated sheet."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Use a coarse open-weave fabric pressed into the clay instead of petals for an all-over texture ring."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "heading": "Ring problems",
          "intro": null,
          "items": [
            {
              "symptom": "Ring cracks at the join after curing",
              "cause": "Join surfaces not pressed firmly together, or overlap too short",
              "fix": "Allow at least 5 mm overlap and press both surfaces together for 10 seconds before curing"
            },
            {
              "symptom": "Petals lift away after curing",
              "cause": "Petals placed on top of the clay rather than embedded flush",
              "fix": "After placing petals, always roll with the rolling pin to press them below the clay surface level"
            }
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
  }
}